Title: THE EQUALIZER - Official Trailer (HD)
Comment:
It's a typical action movie, and there are a lot of cliches in it‚Äîeven the infamous unflinching walk while a fucking giant explosion happens in the background. Also, the bad guys are the typical villains you see in every action movie: overconfident, heavy accent, glass jaw, etc. 

It's similar to John Wick in the sense that a quiet dude with a fucked up past got extremely accurate ninja moves so he can single-handedly take down the entire Russian mafia.

So if you wanna enjoy this, you'll have to be open-minded to the tired tropes. It's an action movie, after all; the cliches are part of the reason we watch 'em.

Personally, I liked the film, and plan on watching the sequel.

Title: THE EQUALIZER - Official Trailer (HD)
Comment:
*WATCH OUT, POSSIBLE SPOILERS BELOW:*



Just watched the movie. Good movie, but in my opinion the trailer gives you expectations which won't truly happen. F.I.:
- There isn't any action during almost the first half of the movie.
- The girl in the trailer is only seen 10 minutes at the start of the movie and 5 minutes in the end of the movie; you barely hear anything about the girl during the movie at all. He basically just felt bad for the girl for a brief moment, but for almost the other 90% of the movie it's about Denzel who becomes the victim instead of the girl, and he only has to protect himself.(probably that's why you almost don't see the girl during the movie at all.)
- There isn't THAT much action in the movie; but for the duration there is, it's good action.
- The ending is very, VERY chippy.

Keep in mind that's just my opinion. I still would rate it high, but I can't recognize the trailer in the movie. Some will probably say the movie was better than the trailer lets you expect, but I say it's the opposite.¬†

TL;DR: Awesome movie, but it's better/different (or worse) than the trailer lets you expect.

Title: THE EQUALIZER - Official Trailer (HD)
Comment: Love the Eminem song but I would feel more excited about seeing this movie if the trailer didn't make it look so generic and if it had a better and more riveting and epic score like the music from the trailer for the movie "The Town" or "The Dark Knight Rises"Nokia trailer! I think it's kinda dull with Denzel wearing the same shirt throughout the whole movie. I would've liked to see him wearing a black trench coat and a fedora or a black leather jacket and turtle neck or a black suit with a tie to make him look more mysterious! I also think Chloe's character could be used for so much more than just the typical damsel-in-distress, she could definitely be of some use to Denzel's character. Lastly, I would feel a lot more confident about this film if it had a different director and screenwriter behind the project, although I have nothing against Antoine Fuqua but I feel that Paul Greengrass (The Bourne Trilogy/Captain Phillips), Tony Gilroy (The Bourne Legacy/Michael Clayton), Brian Helgund, Martin Campbell, Christopher Nolan, Michael Mann, Ridley Scott, The Coen Brothers, or Sam Mendes (007: SkyFall) should've been the director. A film adaptation to The Equalizer should be treated as a well-crated and intelligently written spy/mystery thriller with some action-movie elements and not just a typical, generic popcorn-action thriller but I'm still willing to give it a chance!
